---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Community Guidelines | ParamAI Blog"
  description="The rules that keep ParamAI Blog conversations safe, kind, and useful — especially for our mixed-age student audience."
>
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16">
    <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-brand-600 dark:text-brand-400">
      Community
    </p>
    <h1 class="mt-2 text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight">Community guidelines</h1>
    <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-ink-600 dark:text-ink-300">
      These rules exist because the ParamAI Blog is read by students, including
      students under 18. Keeping conversations safe is not optional — it's why
      the community exists at all.
    </p>

    <div class="prose prose-lg prose-slate mt-10 dark:prose-invert">
      <h2>Who can post</h2>
      <p>
        You must be at least <strong>16 years old</strong> to post comments on this site.
        If you're younger, you're welcome to read everything — but please wait
        before commenting. Many of the topics we discuss (career choices, entrance
        exams, peer pressure) land differently for readers of different ages, and
        we want conversations to stay helpful rather than confusing.
      </p>
      <p>
        Comments are powered by GitHub Discussions via Giscus. GitHub requires an
        account holder to be at least 13, and by commenting here you confirm you
        also meet our 16+ requirement.
      </p>

      <h2>What's welcome</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Sharing your own experiences, learning, and reflections.</li>
        <li>Asking honest questions, even if you think they're "basic".</li>
        <li>Recommending books, courses, YouTube channels, or tools that helped you.</li>
        <li>Polite disagreement and corrections — if we or someone else got something wrong, say so.</li>
        <li>Connecting with other students exploring the same interests.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What's not welcome</h2>
      <h3>1. Personal information (PII)</h3>
      <p>
        Do not post phone numbers, home addresses, school names, full names,
        email addresses, WhatsApp numbers, Instagram handles, or anything else
        that could let strangers contact or identify someone — yours or anyone
        else's. This rule is strict. Comments containing PII are removed on
        sight, regardless of intent.
      </p>
      <p>
        This is also why we deliberately do not offer private messaging. If you
        want to find a study partner or collaborator, do it through the public
        comment thread or through your school.
      </p>

      <h3>2. Harassment, hate, and discrimination</h3>
      <p>
        No insults, slurs, or personal attacks. No discrimination based on caste,
        religion, gender, sexuality, disability, region, or language. If you're
        unsure whether a comment crosses a line, don't post it.
      </p>

      <h3>3. Sexual or suggestive content</h3>
      <p>
        Absolutely not. This is a student-facing site. Posts with sexual content,
        innuendo, or inappropriate imagery are removed immediately and the
        account is reported to GitHub.
      </p>

      <h3>4. Spam, self-promotion, and scams</h3>
      <p>
        Do not post:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Promotional links to your own course, coaching, or business without disclosure.</li>
        <li>"Join my WhatsApp group / Telegram channel" invitations.</li>
        <li>Affiliate links or referral schemes.</li>
        <li>"Guaranteed IIT admission for ₹X" or similar scams. We flag these to authorities.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        If you've written something that's genuinely relevant and it happens to
        be on your own blog, go ahead and link it — as long as that's not the
        entire purpose of your comment.
      </p>

      <h3>5. Political and religious flame wars</h3>
      <p>
        We don't host political debates here. You can mention policy when it's
        directly relevant to a career sector (e.g. the Digital India stack for
        fintech, NEP 2020 for edtech) but please keep it factual. Calls to
        action, partisan attacks, and religious arguments get removed.
      </p>

      <h3>6. Misinformation, especially about exams and admissions</h3>
      <p>
        Do not post false information about JEE, NEET, UPSC, or any entrance
        exam. Do not post fake salary figures, fake placement statistics, or
        made-up "insider" information. Students make life-shaping decisions
        based on what they read — be honest or be quiet.
      </p>

      <h2>Moderation</h2>
      <p>
        New commenters may be pre-moderated, meaning your first comment won't
        be visible until we approve it. This is a one-time thing and keeps the
        spam baseline low.
      </p>
      <p>
        We review all reported comments within 24 hours. Serious violations
        (PII, harassment, sexual content) are removed immediately and the
        account is blocked.
      </p>
      <p>
        Moderation is currently done by the ParamAI team. As the community
        grows we'll add student moderators — if you'd be interested, comment
        on any post with your interest and we'll reach out through a public reply.
      </p>

      <h2>How to report a comment</h2>
      <p>
        Three options, pick whichever is easiest:
      </p>
      <ol>
        <li>
          Click the <strong>three-dot menu</strong> on any comment → <strong>Report</strong>.
          This goes directly to GitHub and to us.
        </li>
        <li>
          Email <a href="mailto:grievance@paramai.in">grievance@paramai.in</a> with
          a link to the comment. We reply within 24 hours.
        </li>
        <li>
          See the <a href="/grievance-officer/">Grievance Officer page</a> for the
          formal complaint process required under Indian IT Rules 2021.
        </li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Consequences of breaking the rules</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>First minor violation:</strong> comment removed, warning via reply.</li>
        <li><strong>Repeated minor violations:</strong> temporary block.</li>
        <li><strong>Major violation</strong> (harassment, PII sharing, sexual content, scam): immediate removal + permanent block + report to GitHub.</li>
        <li>
          <strong>Anything that appears illegal</strong> (threats, child safety issues, fraud):
          reported to the appropriate authorities in addition to the above.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Appeals</h2>
      <p>
        If you think a moderation decision was wrong, email
        <a href="mailto:grievance@paramai.in">grievance@paramai.in</a> with a
        link to the comment and a short explanation. We re-review within 7 days.
      </p>

      <h2>Updates to these guidelines</h2>
      <p>
        We may update these guidelines as the community grows. Material changes
        will be announced in a pinned comment on the home page. Non-material
        changes (wording, structure) happen quietly.
      </p>
      <p>
        <em>Last updated: 9 April 2026.</em>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
